**Why this is the Foundry-parity lever:**
- Foundry's commercial defensibility is *not* the columnar engine (DataFusion + Lance beat it at speed). It's the **enforcement surface** — Object Type permissions wired into every read.
- Our super-domain RBAC fires as a **single masked predicate at the basin boundary** — cheaper than Foundry's per-Object-Type policy evaluation (which scans an ACL table per read).
